Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh. JazakAllahu Khair for sharing your wonderful experience—Al‑hamdulillah that you find the app amazing, helpful, easy to use, and informative. Your kind words encourage us to continue serving the Ummah with tools that bring us closer to the Qur’an and the Sunnah.

If you wish to explore even more blessings, you may:
1. Open the app’s **Qur’an Planner** to set a personalized reading schedule;  
2. Tap the **Audio** section to listen to your favorite reciter or an English translation while you reflect;  
3. Visit **Explore by Topic** to discover deeper knowledge on specific subjects. Should you have any ideas for new features, please submit them at feedback.gtaf.org so we can keep improving for everyone. May Allah accept our efforts and grant you continued benefit. BarakAllahu feekum.

Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh. JazakAllahu Khair for sharing that the app has satisfied all your needs, Alhamdulillah. Your kind words encourage us to continue serving the Ummah with humility and sincerity.  

If you wish to deepen your experience, you may:  
1. Tap the **Menu** ► **Quran Planner** to set a personalized reading schedule;  
2. Choose a reciter or audio translation you love and enable the **Repeat** option for memorization;  
3. Explore **Topics** or **Badges** to discover new insights and track your progress.  

May Allah accept our efforts to bring His Book closer to hearts, and may He reward you for your dedication. BarakAllahu feekum. If you have any further suggestions, please submit them at **feedback.gtaf.org**. May Allah accept from you and us.

Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh. JazakAllahu Khair for sharing your kind words and the du’a for guidance and Jannah. Alhamdulillah that the new version is serving you well—your satisfaction encourages us to keep striving for excellence in serving the Ummah with a reliable Qur’an companion.  

If you wish to explore more of the app’s blessings, you may:  
1. Open the **Quran Planner** to set daily reading goals;  
2. Try the **Mushaf Mode** or various reciters to enrich your recitation;  
3. Visit the **Library** to bookmark, take notes, and earn badges for consistency.  
Should you have any ideas for future features or notice anything to improve, please submit them at **feedback.gtaf.org** so we can serve you better. May Allah accept our efforts and grant you and us success. BarakAllahu feekum.

Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh. JazakAllahu Khair for sharing your wonderful experience—knowing that the app makes reading the Qur’an easy truly lifts our hearts and encourages us to continue serving the Ummah with dedication.

To enrich your journey even further, you may:  
1. Tap the **Audio** icon to listen to your favorite reciter while you read;  
2. Explore the **Translations & Tafsīr** menu for deeper understanding in your preferred language;  
3. Use the **Qur’an Planner** to set a daily reading goal that fits your schedule.  

May Allah accept your sincere reading and grant you ease in all your ibādah. BarakAllahu feekum.

Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh. JazakAllahu Khair for sharing your kind words—Al‑ḥamdu li‑llāh that you find the app “very nice to understand.” Your encouragement lifts our hearts and reminds us of the blessing of serving the Ummah with a tool that eases the connection to the Qur’an.  

If you wish to deepen your experience, you may:  
1️⃣ Tap the menu icon and select **Audio Recitations** to listen to your favorite qāriʾs;  
2️⃣ Open the **Qur’an Planner** to set a personal reading schedule and track daily progress;  
3️⃣ Explore the **Topic Explorer** for themed tafsīr and lessons that enrich understanding.  

May Allah accept your good intentions and grant you continued ease in learning His Book. BarakAllahu feekum.

Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh. JazakAllahu Khair for sharing your kind words—Al‑hamdulillah that the prayer‑time feature is serving you well. Your appreciation encourages us to continue serving the Ummah with reliable tools for our daily Ibadah.  

If you ever wish to tailor the prayer‑time experience further, you can open the app, go to **Settings → Prayer Times**, and:  
1. Choose your preferred calculation method;  
2. Enable or adjust notification times;  
3. Turn on automatic location detection for even more accurate timings.  

Should you have any other ideas—such as a Qibla compass or an Islamic calendar—please let us know by submitting feedback at **feedback.gtaf.org**, so we can consider them for future updates. May Allah accept our efforts and bless your worship. BarakAllahu feekum.
